Sentencas: The effect of ZnO addition on the sinterability and ionic conductivity of Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 is investigated.
Titulo: Sinterability and electrical properties of ZnO-doped Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 electrolytes prepared by an EDTA-citrate complexing method

Sentencas: Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 is prepared using an EDTA-citrate complexing method in order to further improve its electrical properties.
Titulo: Sinterability and electrical properties of ZnO-doped Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 electrolytes prepared by an EDTA-citrate complexing method

Sentencas: Using a ZnO content over 1 mol%, the sinterability of Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 is significantly improved by reducing the sintering temperature from 1500 to 1350 degrees C and a relative density of above 95% was achieved.
Titulo: Sinterability and electrical properties of ZnO-doped Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 electrolytes prepared by an EDTA-citrate complexing method

Sentencas: The highest ionic conductivity of 0.0516 S cm(-1) was obtained at 750 degrees C for (YDC)(0.99)(ZnO)(0.01) sintered at 1350 degrees C. Pure YDC sintered at 1500 degrees C, on the other hand, yielded 0.0289 S cm(-1).
Titulo: Sinterability and electrical properties of ZnO-doped Ce0.8Y0.2O1.9 electrolytes prepared by an EDTA-citrate complexing method
